-2"},"57:1–2"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/82.14"},"82:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/97.21"},"97:21"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/a-of-f/1.10"},"Articles of Faith 1:10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.19"},"Moses 7:19"],". Note that this lesson will focus on Zion as the society that is established by people who have become pure in heart through the gospel of Jesus Christ.)"]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","What characterized the Zion of Enoch’s time? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.12-19"},"Moses 7:12–19"],".) Why was their city called Zion? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.18"},"Moses 7:18"],".) What does it mean to be “of one heart and one mind”?"]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Why were the early Saints unable to build the city of Zion? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/101.6-8"},"D&C 101:6–8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/105.1-12"},"105:1–12"],".) What can we learn from their experience that can help us build Zion today?"]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/82.14-15"},"D&C 82:14–15"],". What did the Lord command in these verses? What are some specific things you should do to build Zion?"]]],["div",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-46-zion-the-pure-in-heart.p8"},"Think of some of the most meaningful teachings you remember from this year’s study of the Doctrine and Covenants and Church history. Some ways to help remember could include looking back through this study guide, reviewing scripture chains, recalling favorite stories from",["span.emphasis","Our Heritage,"],"or leafing through the Doctrine and Covenants to see passages you have marked."],["div",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-histor